    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix encode_u8_service_type function to properly return service type value\n\n### Summary\nThe `encode_u8_service_type` function in ServiceType.c was incorrectly implemented, causing issues with service type encoding in NAS messages. The function was creating unnecessary buffers and returning full bytes instead of just the service type value.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/ServiceType.c`: Simplified the `encode_u8_service_type` function to directly return the service type value masked to 4 bits, matching the expected behavior and usage patterns in other NAS encoding functions.\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen sending Extended Service Request messages, the service type field was not being encoded correctly, leading to malformed NAS messages. This could be observed in network traces where the service type value in the initial byte of the message was incorrect, causing potential interoperability issues with network equipment.\n"
}